@codelipenghui The properties were meant to be completely application defined. That also might confuse some application that has its own set of keys to suddenly see a new key there. 

In general, I'd prefer to have a `Message.getRedeliveryCount()` method instead, to have a clear separation from users vs system info. Additionally, this also improve discoverability of the feature.

If we foresee to need add multiple of these method, a context object would also be an option, though it would be probably far-fetched at this point.
